This article is a transcript of remarks made by President Trump and Chairman Kim at a meeting in Hanoi, Vietnam. They discuss their previous meeting in Singapore and the progress made since then. Chairman Kim mentions misunderstandings and past hostility, but expresses hope for success. President Trump thanks Chairman Kim and expresses his satisfaction with the first summit. He also praises Vietnam and expresses his belief in the country's economic potential. The remarks end with President Trump declining to comment on Michael Cohen's testimony.